14#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
15#include <cstdint>
16#endif
17
18#include <limits>
19
20#include "absl/types/optional.h"
21
22namespace webrtc {
23
24template <typename U>
25inline bool IsNewer(U value, U prev_value) {
26 static_assert(!std::numeric_limits<U>::is_signed, "U must be unsigned");
27 // kBreakpoint is the half-way mark for the type U. For instance, for a
28 // uint16_t it will be 0x8000, and for a uint32_t, it will be 0x8000000.
29 constexpr U kBreakpoint = (std::numeric_limits<U>::max() >> 1) + 1;
30 // Distinguish between elements that are exactly kBreakpoint apart.
31 // If t1>t2 and |t1-t2| = kBreakpoint: IsNewer(t1,t2)=true,
32 // IsNewer(t2,t1)=false
33 // rather than having IsNewer(t1,t2) = IsNewer(t2,t1) = false.
34 if (value - prev_value == kBreakpoint) {
35 return value > prev_value;
36 }
37 return value != prev_value &&
38 static_cast<U>(value - prev_value) < kBreakpoint;
39}
40
41// Utility class to unwrap a number to a larger type. The numbers will never be
42// unwrapped to a negative value.
43template <typename U>
44class Unwrapper {
45 static_assert(!std::numeric_limits<U>::is_signed, "U must be unsigned");
46 static_assert(std::numeric_limits<U>::max() <=
47 std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max(),
48 "U must not be wider than 32 bits");
49
50 public:
51 // Get the unwrapped value, but don't update the internal state.
52 int64_t UnwrapWithoutUpdate(U value) const {
53 if (!last_value_)
54 return value;
55
56 constexpr int64_t kMaxPlusOne =
57 static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<U>::max()) + 1;
58
59 U cropped_last = static_cast<U>(*last_value_);
60 int64_t delta = value - cropped_last;
61 if (IsNewer(value, cropped_last)) {
62 if (delta < 0)
63 delta += kMaxPlusOne; // Wrap forwards.
64 } else if (delta > 0 && (*last_value_ + delta - kMaxPlusOne) >= 0) {
65 // If value is older but delta is positive, this is a backwards
66 // wrap-around. However, don't wrap backwards past 0 (unwrapped).
67 delta -= kMaxPlusOne;
68 }
69
70 return *last_value_ + delta;
71 }
72
73 // Only update the internal state to the specified last (unwrapped) value.
74 void UpdateLast(int64_t last_value) { last_value_ = last_value; }
75
76 // Unwrap the value and update the internal state.
77 int64_t Unwrap(U value) {
78 int64_t unwrapped = UnwrapWithoutUpdate(value);
79 UpdateLast(unwrapped);
80 return unwrapped;
81 }
82
83 private:
84 absl::optional<int64_t> last_value_;
85};
86
87using SequenceNumberUnwrapper = Unwrapper<uint16_t>;
88using TimestampUnwrapper = Unwrapper<uint32_t>;
89
90// NB: Doesn't fulfill strict weak ordering requirements.
91// Mustn't be used as std::map Compare function.
92inline bool IsNewerSequenceNumber(uint16_t sequence_number,
93 uint16_t prev_sequence_number) {
94 return IsNewer(sequence_number, prev_sequence_number);
95}
96
97// NB: Doesn't fulfill strict weak ordering requirements.
98// Mustn't be used as std::map Compare function.
99inline bool IsNewerTimestamp(uint32_t timestamp, uint32_t prev_timestamp) {
100 return IsNewer(timestamp, prev_timestamp);
101}
102
103inline uint16_t LatestSequenceNumber(uint16_t sequence_number1,
104 uint16_t sequence_number2) {
105 return IsNewerSequenceNumber(sequence_number1, sequence_number2)
106 ? sequence_number1
107 : sequence_number2;
108}
109
110inline uint32_t LatestTimestamp(uint32_t timestamp1, uint32_t timestamp2) {
111 return IsNewerTimestamp(timestamp1, timestamp2) ? timestamp1 : timestamp2;
112}

114} // namespace webrtc
